<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,290,858]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,650,677]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Habitat:</emphasis>
Pine-douglas fir forest (clearings within the forest where shrubs and grasses are dominant) vegetation 
<typeStatus box="[151,203,688,714]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
. Local population occurred in canyon along dry intermittent streambed (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lavigne, R. J." box="[1058,1231,687,714]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="270 - 273" refId="ref104681" refString="Lavigne, R. J. (1970 b) Courtship and predation behavior of Heteropogon maculinervis (Diptera: Asilidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 43, 270 - 273." type="journal article" year="1970">Lavigne 1970b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,290,858]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,723,749]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Ethology:</emphasis>
Flies rested and foraged from tips of branches of willow and box elder at a height of 1.2–6.1 m; courtship (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lavigne, R. J." box="[314,488,759,786]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="270 - 273" refId="ref104681" refString="Lavigne, R. J. (1970 b) Courtship and predation behavior of Heteropogon maculinervis (Diptera: Asilidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 43, 270 - 273." type="journal article" year="1970">Lavigne 1970b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
